A 200 level student of Accounting at Obafemi Awolowo University Ile-Ife, Osun State, Emmanuel Adedeji, who committed suicide is said to have lost his father recently. His mother arrived on the campus on Wednesday alongside family members to claim his corpse. He was said to have drunk insecticide on Tuesday leading to his death. Findings by Daily Trust showed that Adedeji is the last child of the family and the only son. The Public Relation Officer of the university, Mr Abiodun Olarewaju, described the death of the students as unfortunate.